The 32 Artillery Brigade of the Nigeria Army has disowned one Corporal Innocent Victor who was arrested and paraded by the Nigeria police for armed robbery. Corporal Victor had claimed to be serving with the 32 Artillery Brigade. He was arrested alongside one Police Constable, David Friday after allegedly robbing some persons in Idanre local government. Spokesman to the 32 Artillery Brigade, Captain Ayorinde Omojokun, in a press statement said Victor was not a serving Army personnel of 32 Artillery Brigade and has never worked as a Nigerian Army personnel. The Nation By Muftau Ogunyemi Okitipupa (Ondo State) - The Nigerian Army, has said that no fewer than 31 suspects were arrested and 14 dane guns recovered in a Crocodile Smile IV operation  in Ondo State. Brig. – Gen. Zakari Abubakar, the Commander of 32 Artillery Brigade made this disclosure at the… December 23, 2019 In "News" PORT HARCOURT (Sundiata Post) - The Rivers State chapter of the All Progressives Congress (APC) has expressed shock that the Governor Nyesom Wike Administration has dropped charges against three notorious armed robbery suspects alleged to have killed police and army personnel. A statement signed by Dr. Davies Ikanya and sent… January 13, 2016 In "Top Stories" By Bamigbola Gbolagunte, Akure A 300-level student (name withheld) of the Ondo State Government-owned Adekunle Ajasin University, Akungba-Akoko, was allegedly raped on Wednesday, by soldiers attached to the 32 Artillery Brigade of the Nigeria Army, Owena, Akure. Daily Sun gathered that the incident occurred at the military checkpoint at Ikare-Akoko,… August 2, 2019 In "Metro"